2. The HTTP protocol is a request/response protocol. Once the TCP/IP connection is established, a client application
sends a request to the server application (GatewayTB) a then waits for the response. In the request message, the client,
accordingly to the HTTP protocol, sends the HTTP version it can manage; the behavior of the server depends on such
version: if the client requested HTTP 1.0 then the server, as soon as it has sent the response, closes the connection; if the client requested HTTP 1.1, the server, after sending the response, waits for a new request on the same connection until a
configured timeout (since the last request) elapses or the client itself closes the connection.
